Rules:
- Title: descriptive, role-appropriate
- Summary: 2-3 sentences, what the reader will learn
- Content: full markdown with steps, explanations, and inline code
- Code examples: use the reader's tech stack when possible, include language and description
- Citations: reference the retrieved chunks by chunk_id, source_url, and source_title
- Key takeaways: up to 5 bullet points
- Warnings: common pitfalls specific to this role
- Prerequisites: what the reader should have done/understood before this section
- Estimated time: realistic minutes for this role and experience level
- Progressive complexity: section 1 = basics, section {total_sections} = advanced patterns
- Do NOT repeat content from previous sections
